Basic Installation
==================
To compile you need header files for 
glib 2.32 or newer
gtk 3.4 or newer (for Xorg server)
libvte 0.30.1 or newer
vala 0.16 or newer

Type `make' to compile the package.

Type `make install' to install the programs and any data files and
documentation.  When installing into a prefix owned by root, it is
recommended that the package be configured and built as a regular
user, and only the `make install' phase executed with root
privileges.

By default program will installed into /usr, you can override install
directory by PREFIX variable.
For example: `PREFIX=/usr/local make install'
